"""
    Write a function which sorts the given list of integers
    in ascending order according to the sum of their digits.
    Note: if there are several items with similar sum of their digits,
    order them based on their index in original list.

    For example:
    >>> order_by_points([1, 11, -1, -11, -12]) == [-1, -11, 1, -12, 11]
    >>> order_by_points([]) == []
    """

"""
    Ek function likho jo diye gaye integers ki list ko unke digits ka sum ke hisaab se ascending order mein sort karta hai.
    Dhyan do: agar kuch items ke digits ka sum baraabar ho, 
    toh unhe di gayi list me unke index ke hisaab se order karo.

    Jaise ki:
    >>> order_by_points([1, 11, -1, -11, -12]) == [-1, -11, 1, -12, 11]
    >>> order_by_points([]) == []
"""